BREAKING: Tropical Storm Fred made landfall Monday afternoon near Cape San Blas, Florida. Maximum sustained winds were estimated at 65 mph.

Thousands have already lost power along the coast as the storm’s strong winds and heavy rain move ashore. Tune to The Weather Channel for all the latest details on this developing situation.

🎥: @noaa

#Fred #Florida #storm #weather #GulfCoast

node.text:
The Dixie Fire, the largest wildfire currently burning in the U.S., is threatening nearly 15,000 structures. The blaze has already destroyed more than 1,000 homes and businesses since it began in mid-July.  The Dixie Fire has burned more than 890 square miles so far and was 31% contained on Monday. 

Weekend thunderstorms fueled the fire’s advance into Taylorsville, California, where several structures burned. The accompanying rain did little to help. 

Click the link in our bio to read more.

Photo by AP/Eugene Garcia

#Wildfire #DixieFire #CaliforniaWildfire

node.text:
One major reason hurricanes and tropical storms are dangerous weather phenomena is because they can cause catastrophic flash flooding.

Floods have led to $260 billion in damage in the U.S. over the past 30 years, and over 100 deaths annually, on average, since 2015.

Since Tropical Storm Fred is forecast to drop a lot of rain on the Southeast over the next few days, tap the link in our bio for a few tips to help keep you and your loved ones safer (and drier) in a flood.

📸 : Fajrin Raharjo Raharjo/EyeEm/Getty Images

#floods #Fred #weather #TropicalStorm #safety

node.text:
Tropical Storm Fred is expected to make landfall Monday along the Florida Panhandle.

It will bring flooding rain, gusty winds, storm surge and isolated tornadoes.

Soaking rainfall and possible flooding from Fred and its remnant will also spread inland across parts of Alabama, Georgia, the western Carolinas and mid-Atlantic region.

We are constantly tracking all the latest developments on The Weather Channel and The Weather Channel app, so tune in and log on for all the latest.

Tap the link in our bio for the complete forecast and tag your friends who are in the path of this storm.

node.text:
Hundreds have been killed in a 7.2-magnitude earthquake that struck Haiti on Saturday morning, and at least 1,800 people have been injured. Rescue efforts continue on Sunday, but Tropical Storm Grace is expected to bring heavy rain with the possibility of flash flooding and mudslides late Monday, which could make the disaster much worse. 

Prime Minister Ariel Henry said that some towns were completely destroyed in the quake. Photos show major damage in Les Cayes in southwestern Haiti, with lopsided buildings and homes reduced to piles of rubble.

Click the links in our bio to read more.

Photos by AP/Joseph Odelyn

A tropical storm warning has been issued for a part of the Florida Gulf Coast ahead of Tropical Storm Fred's expected landfall early this week.

The tropical storm warning extends along the Florida Panhandle from Navarre to the Wakulla/Jefferson County line. This means tropical storm conditions (39+ mph winds) are expected in the warning area beginning Monday.

A tropical storm watch remains in effect in the Florida Panhandle from the border between Alabama and Florida to Navarre.

node.text:
Hundreds of people are dead after a major earthquake rocked Haiti Saturday morning.

That number is expected to continue to climb as more of the rubble is searched. The country's disaster agency said Saturday afternoon that hundreds of others were injured or missing.

Recovery efforts could be complicated by the weather. There is a possibility that Tropical Storm Grace could impact Haiti with heavy rain and strong winds in the coming days. Heavy rain could compound the disaster with flooding and landslides.

Entire towns were left nearly flattened by the earthquake, and the prime minister declared a one-month state of emergency for the entire country.

Tap the link in our bio to read more.

📷: Delot Jean @apnews

#earthquake #Haiti #TropicalStormGrace

And now there's Grace.

Puerto Rico is under a tropical storm warning as Tropical Storm Grace formed several hundred miles to the east.

The system could follow Fred's path near the Greater Antilles into next week. Tropical storm watches and warnings have been issued in the eastern Caribbean. Florida is in the cone of uncertainty.
